After 9/11, the focus shifted from Al-Qaeda to militant Islam.
A memo argued for preemptive military action against terrorists and their supporters, even if not linked to 9/11.
The memo gave the President broad authority to protect the US.
Gonzales played a key role in creating the legal framework for actions like Guantanamo.
Yoo clarified that advice from the Office of Legal Counsel was not influenced by the White House.
The debate over torture and interrogation practices continues, with calls for accountability and transparency.
The need for a full accounting to restore the nation's image and uphold human dignity is emphasized.
